Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Conan Episode 863 "The \NSpirit Detective's Murder (Part One)"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.39,0:00:08.36,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Rum.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.02,0:00:11.63,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.20,0:00:15.85,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The person who vanished after killing \NHaneda Koji seventeen years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.85,0:00:19.97,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,...was the bodyguard Asaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.35,0:00:21.76,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And the identity of Asaka...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.26,0:00:27.27,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,...is the number two man of the \NBlack Organization, Rum.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.81,0:00:33.59,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Even if that's the dying message \Nhe left before he was murdered,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.20,0:00:36.84,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I can't find any other information.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.82,0:00:41.02,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Is Asaka their family name \Nor given name, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.75,0:00:45.21,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If it's their family name, then \NI can't even tell their gender.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.31,0:00:50.00,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And what drug was Haneda Koji given?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.62,0:00:53.88,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently it was made by Haibara's parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.88,0:00:56.41,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But Haibara said she wasn't trying...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.59,0:01:00.09,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,...to make a poison when \Nshe recreated the drug.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.27,0:01:06.00,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, Gin mentioned something \Nwhen I was given that drug.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.35,0:01:09.00,DCItalic,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,We'll use this.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.80,0:01:14.01,DCItalic,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,This drug was recently developed \Nby the Organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.32,0:01:18.01,DCItalic,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,They won't be able to find any \Ntraces of poison in the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.30,0:01:20.98,DCItalic,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,It allows you to commit the perfect crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.76,0:01:25.64,DCItalic,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,Although this prototype hasn't \Nbeen tested on humans yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.87,0:01:32.92,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Which means I was given the \Nthe drug recreated by Haibara,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.92,0:01:35.78,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and I was its first test subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.29,0:01:36.87,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm home.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.87,0:01:38.28,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What? An interview?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.75,0:01:41.28,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,With another detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.63,0:01:45.29,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Spirit detective Hotta Gaito?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.62,0:01:50.30,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I remember a shady detective \Nwho used to go by that name.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.30,0:01:53.71,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, I need to \Ngather more information.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.04,0:01:58.65,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But the case's site was taken down, and \Nit hasn't been reuploaded for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.65,0:02:03.11,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What? He's going to solve the \Nmystery of Haneda Koji's murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.11,0:02:03.92,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.44,0:02:06.68,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Wasn't the Haneda Koji murder...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.68,0:02:11.38,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,...an unsolved case of some guy...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.38,0:02:13.46,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,...who was murdered in America \Nseventeen years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.16,0:02:15.95,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.41,0:02:18.57,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He's going to summon the \Nspirit of Haneda Koji?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.07,0:02:22.02,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have time for that kind of idiocy!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.86,0:02:23.80,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.80,0:02:27.06,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,This time it's just a short segment\Non a late night TV show,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.06,0:02:30.37,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,but if it's well-received, it'll \Nbe switched to prime time?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.37,0:02:32.33,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,And my name will be in the title?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.33,0:02:36.92,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,And the MC will be Okino Yoko-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.42,0:02:36.92,Mori,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Mori Kogoro's
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.42,0:02:36.92,Cold,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Solve the Cold Case!!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.58,0:02:43.38,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,There's a planning meeting tomorrow \Nmorning at a hotel restaurant?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.38,0:02:45.27,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.68,0:02:47.74,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,So, how much does it pay?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.44,0:03:02.11,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Even heaven is watching the \Nlabyrinths of the world!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.33,0:03:04.07,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Full throttle reasoning skills \Npenetrate all mysteries!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.54,0:03:06.70,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The information on Rum is eerily effective.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.70,0:03:08.60,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What will the spirit detective reveal?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.60,0:03:10.54,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.54,0:03:12.78,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,...with the body of a child \Nand the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.78,0:03:15.28,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.39,0:04:50.01,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,The Spirit Detective's Murder \N(Part One)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.67,0:04:48.44,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"The Spirit Detective's Murder, Part One!"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.96,0:04:56.57,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Why'd you have to come with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.57,0:05:00.90,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Ran-neechan's been gone since yesterday \Nnight because of her karate training camp.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.32,0:05:04.82,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And it's not fair that you're the \Nonly one who gets to eat at a hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.82,0:05:08.18,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently the TV station's paying for it,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.18,0:05:10.91,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,but don't order anything too expensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.23,0:05:16.08,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, I want to meet \Nthe spirit detective, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.50,0:05:16.08,Gaito,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Hotta Gaito \NSpirit Detective
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.39,0:05:19.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That detective Hotta \NGaito summons the spirits...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.00,0:05:21.34,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,...of dead people and says \Nthings only people close...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.34,0:05:25.80,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,...to the deceased would've known, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.80,0:05:26.47,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.73,0:05:31.99,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently he found the skeleton of a \Nperson who went missing in the mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.99,0:05:33.74,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It was a coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.15,0:05:36.73,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The bones ended up belonging to someone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.10,0:05:41.79,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, Hotta knew all that information \Nbecause he investigated cases beforehand.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.18,0:05:47.54,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It got out that he paid people to create \Nfalse witness reports of the missing person.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.93,0:05:51.07,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,After the media destroyed \Nhim, he disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.76,0:05:55.24,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, I'm surprised he \Nwas able to return to TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.68,0:05:59.46,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,And even if he does have a new scam,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.46,0:06:02.67,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,the Sleeping Kogoro will expose it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.27,0:06:06.17,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.76,0:06:13.72,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If he's summoning the spirit \Nof a man who died so long ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.72,0:06:19.11,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,it's likely he got a hold of information related \Nto the case that hasn't been made public yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.93,0:06:23.32,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'll do whatever it takes \Nto get that information.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.18,0:06:26.28,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And expose the identity of Rum.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.03,0:06:34.33,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.24,0:06:37.83,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.37,0:06:40.71,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Sorry for asking you to come so early.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.37,0:06:42.29,Sanpei,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Kokuri Sanpei (35) \NToto TV Director
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.71,0:06:41.72,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.50,0:06:45.37,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, you must be Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.37,0:06:46.67,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.89,0:06:48.27,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,I know about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.27,0:06:49.99,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,You're the Kid Killer, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.99,0:06:54.16,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,You think we could get a \Ncomment from you, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.16,0:06:54.84,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.42,0:06:58.45,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Let's eat while we discuss the show.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.45,0:07:02.28,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,First, we need to go the room \Nwhere Hotta-san is staying.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.28,0:07:02.94,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.40,0:07:06.90,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently he wants you to \Nsee him summon a spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.90,0:07:07.78,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.83,0:07:11.06,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,Let's head there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.43,0:07:18.48,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, you were right to \Nbring Conan-kun with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.48,0:07:19.29,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.70,0:07:22.72,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,Even if him summoning a spirit \Ndoes seem a little fake,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.72,0:07:25.44,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,we'll still be able to get a \Nshot of him looking surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.44,0:07:26.34,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.76,0:07:29.63,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I can't imagine this kid \Nbeing surprised by that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.71,0:07:36.72,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? That's weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.72,0:07:38.85,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,He should be in his room.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.38,0:07:43.29,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,When I emailed him this morning to \Nconfirm the time of our meeting,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.29,0:07:47.86,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,he said he was seeing someone \Nelse before our meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.86,0:07:50.74,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe he's still at their room.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.28,0:07:54.95,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Hotta-san emailed me an hour ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.49,0:07:56.12,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.12,0:07:58.99,Kill,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,They're going to kill me. Help.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.88,0:07:58.99,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,"Th-They're going to kill me. Help?"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.99,0:08:00.86,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.26,0:08:05.55,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,I-In any case, I'll have a \Nbellhop come unlock the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.55,0:08:09.77,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,You stay here so nobody leaves the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.77,0:08:11.09,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.03,0:08:15.90,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,This better not be some kind of performance.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.69,0:08:21.98,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What's taking him so long?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.98,0:08:24.56,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What is that director doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.56,0:08:25.85,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, they're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.34,0:08:29.86,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. It took a while \Nto explain the situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.26,0:08:33.48,DCMain,BELLHOP,0000,0000,0000,,Hotta-sama?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.25,0:08:36.40,DCMain,BELLHOP,0000,0000,0000,,Hotta-sama, are you there?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.40,0:08:38.62,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need to bother \Nwith that. Open the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.79,0:08:40.84,DCMain,BELLHOP,0000,0000,0000,,A-All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.84,0:08:41.41,DCMain,BELLHOP,0000,0000,0000,,In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.38,0:08:43.42,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.33,0:08:45.24,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,My phone's ringing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.21,0:08:47.71,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, Hotta-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.17,0:08:49.25,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,Is that you, Hotta-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.06,0:08:51.09,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.49,0:08:53.11,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,It was a wrong number.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.11,0:08:54.74,DCMain,BELLHOP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm opening the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.74,0:08:55.60,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.04,0:08:59.35,DCMain,BELLHOP,0000,0000,0000,,Hotta-sama?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.45,0:09:02.81,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What was that sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.10,0:09:04.58,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It sounded like something breaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.81,0:09:14.66,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Wineglasses and plates.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.21,0:09:18.60,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like someone was drinking \Nwine until a moment ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.36,0:09:25.22,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That person dropped the plates and \Nglasses in surprise when we came in,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.22,0:09:28.18,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,stepped in the spilled wine, \Nand ran into that room.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.26,0:09:46.27,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Someone just ran from the balcony!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.57,0:09:48.06,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But we're on the fourth floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.42,0:09:50.87,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,No, I know I saw someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.76,0:09:55.72,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,They must've crossed the balcony \Ninto the room next door.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.39,0:09:59.76,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,They left their wine-stained \Nslippers behind, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.76,0:10:00.78,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That must be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.06,0:10:04.62,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, bellhop.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.62,0:10:05.81,DCMain,BELLHOP,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.40,0:10:09.00,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Is there someone staying \Nin the room next door?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.00,0:10:11.71,DCMain,BELLHOP,0000,0000,0000,,You mean room 403?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.20,0:10:15.96,DCMain,BELLHOP,0000,0000,0000,,A young high school-aged man has \Nbeen staying there since last week.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.24,0:10:17.08,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.58,0:10:20.97,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Some kid has been living by \Nthemselves in a hotel for a week?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.28,0:10:25.22,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, what's that sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.72,0:10:28.56,DCMain,BELLHOP,0000,0000,0000,,It's the sound of the remodeling \Nconstruction going on downstairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.56,0:10:30.60,DCMain,BELLHOP,0000,0000,0000,,Since it's loud and makes \Nthe rooms shake a little,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.60,0:10:33.78,DCMain,BELLHOP,0000,0000,0000,,the rooms in this area are discounted.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.78,0:10:34.90,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.34,0:10:39.16,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,So, where's Hotta Gaito?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.56,0:10:40.78,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Probably in bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.38,0:10:42.97,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There's a slight bump.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.94,0:10:50.17,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But judging by the fact that \Nhe hasn't moved an inch,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.80,0:10:52.29,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,he's probably already...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.86,0:11:15.44,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it. Who would do something so awful?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.45,0:11:17.56,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,Hotta-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.20,0:11:19.08,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,Hotta-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.08,0:11:19.53,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.20,0:11:21.63,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Don't touch the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.63,0:11:22.82,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.82,0:11:26.45,DCMain,BELLHOP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go back to the front \Ndesk and call the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.73,0:11:30.20,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,No, you stay here with Kokuri-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.20,0:11:32.13,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,...and call the police from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.13,0:11:34.79,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,If the killer returns through that window,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.79,0:11:38.19,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,one man may not be enough to stop them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.19,0:11:40.29,DCMain,BELLHOP,0000,0000,0000,,S-Stop them?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.29,0:11:41.88,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,M-Mori-san, where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.40,0:11:44.68,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to the room next door.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.68,0:11:49.29,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That kid living in the room next \Ndoor may have been killed already.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.99,0:11:57.40,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it. No one's answering.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.66,0:11:59.81,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The killer must've gotten to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.81,0:12:01.90,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.20,0:12:03.91,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,What's with all the noise?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.52,0:12:06.45,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.84,0:12:12.08,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? You're the guy from \Nthe detective agency.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.32,0:12:14.96,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sera...neechan?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.20,0:12:17.88,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Conan-kun's with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.10,0:12:21.87,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, did anyone enter your room?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.75,0:12:24.26,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.57,0:12:26.04,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.04,0:12:27.26,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,It's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.57,0:12:30.27,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the only one in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.02,0:12:35.77,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I see, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.05,0:12:37.98,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Have I got this right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.98,0:12:40.89,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,The room next door to this one is room 402.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.89,0:12:44.55,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,You went there with TV director Kokuri...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.55,0:12:47.25,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,...to meet with the spirit detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.25,0:12:49.16,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,The moment you opened the door,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.40,0:12:52.66,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,you heard the sound of wine glasses...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.66,0:12:57.95,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,...and plates falling and breaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.38,0:13:01.92,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,When you ran into the room, you saw footprints \Nleft by someone who stepped in the wine.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.16,0:13:05.18,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Those footprints led into the bedroom, so \Nwhen you opened the door and went inside,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.51,0:13:09.97,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,the window was open, and you saw \Nsomeone running from the balcony.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.26,0:13:16.60,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,That balcony is connected to the \Nbalcony of my room, room 403.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.96,0:13:21.00,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,You thought that person might have leapt...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.00,0:13:23.86,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,...over the railing and fled into my room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.38,0:13:25.88,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,While you were looking around,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.88,0:13:29.87,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,you noticed a slight lump \Nin the bed in the bedroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.06,0:13:32.37,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,And when you pulled off the covers...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.65,0:13:35.87,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.09,0:13:36.72,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.14,0:13:41.82,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's why we were wondering if \Nanyone suspicious came to your room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.22,0:13:44.33,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,It's just me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.33,0:13:48.01,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But the wine-stained slippers were left at the \Nedge of the balcony of the room next door.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.47,0:13:51.51,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Since we're on the fourth floor,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.18,0:13:56.27,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,your room was the only \Nplace they could've gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.49,0:13:59.12,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, let me search your room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.12,0:14:01.98,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,They could have sneaked in \Nand be hiding somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.98,0:14:04.48,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I told you, there's no one here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.06,0:14:08.70,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, do you know who did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.70,0:14:12.19,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently he met someone \Nbefore he was meeting me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.19,0:14:14.16,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,They probably did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.65,0:14:18.80,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably someone involved \Nin that seventeen year old case.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.26,0:14:22.23,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Hotta Gaito said he was going to \Nsummon the spirit of Haneda Koji,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.23,0:14:25.67,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,who was murdered in that case.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.23,0:14:27.67,DCItalic,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,H-Haneda...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.20,0:14:29.18,DCItalic,SISTER,0000,0000,0000,,...Koji.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.18,0:14:30.15,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.15,0:14:33.00,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Did that detective tell you \Nanything about the case?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.00,0:14:35.35,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,N-No. I hadn't met him yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.64,0:14:38.77,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What? Do you know something about Haneda?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.80,0:14:43.15,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah. He was a professional \Nshogi player, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.34,0:14:47.57,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to be involved in this \Ncase, let me search your room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.94,0:14:50.96,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The police will be doing it \Nanyway when they get here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.96,0:14:52.66,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.34,0:14:57.79,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I left my underwear out, so give me a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.94,0:15:02.17,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.35,0:15:05.29,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,How long does it take to \Nput away some underwear?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.75,0:15:07.88,DCMain,BELLHOP,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.88,0:15:10.18,DCMain,BELLHOP,0000,0000,0000,,I just heard from the front desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.67,0:15:14.53,DCMain,BELLHOP,0000,0000,0000,,We received a complaint about a car parked \Nin a strange spot in the parking lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.53,0:15:16.93,DCMain,BELLHOP,0000,0000,0000,,Is it either of yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.93,0:15:19.43,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's my car.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.95,0:15:23.52,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. The parking lot was full.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.52,0:15:26.97,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,I forgot that I was going to re-park it later.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.97,0:15:29.24,DCMain,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'll move it right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.44,0:15:33.76,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.76,0:15:35.30,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wa-
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.65,0:15:38.45,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If you needed to hide yourself in a hurry...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.16,0:15:41.64,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The perfect place would be the balcony.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.19,0:15:46.54,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But there's no one here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.99,0:15:52.55,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, since the wine-stained slippers \Nwere on the balcony next door,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.09,0:15:56.00,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,they must have jumped to this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.47,0:15:58.06,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,This is the fourth floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.32,0:16:00.41,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They couldn't have jumped down.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.06,0:16:04.81,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? There's a car parked \Ndirectly below the balcony.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.20,0:16:06.88,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's it doing there?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.53,0:16:09.44,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Kokuri-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.48,0:16:13.82,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that must be the car he just mentioned.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.36,0:16:16.51,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's a convertible.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.95,0:16:18.68,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He's got a nice car.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.46,0:16:21.83,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's odd, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.74,0:16:25.35,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The parking lot's pretty empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.56,0:16:28.13,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why'd he park it there?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.03,0:16:35.97,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I should take some pictures just in case.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.28,0:16:57.41,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I should take one of under the balcony, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.40,0:17:00.33,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.14,0:17:04.10,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Kogoro-san's calling you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.10,0:17:06.04,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,He's finished searching the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.04,0:17:07.49,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.89,0:17:09.53,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to have bothered you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.78,0:17:15.26,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,See? I was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.65,0:17:18.01,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't he have good instincts?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.65,0:17:23.02,DCMain,SISTER,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, solve this \Ncase as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.60,0:17:28.52,DCMain,SISTER,0000,0000,0000,,If the police search this room, \Nthey'll find out about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.49,0:17:33.07,DCMain,SISTER,0000,0000,0000,,You need to solve it before \Nthey hear about the information...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.18,0:17:36.69,DCMain,SISTER,0000,0000,0000,,...concerning Haneda Koji's \Nmurder and come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.21,0:17:39.78,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.17,0:17:49.39,DCItalic,SISTER,0000,0000,0000,,A bow tie?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.21,0:18:04.43,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I understand the events leading \Nup to the discovery of the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.86,0:18:09.86,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,But it's hard to believe someone \Nhurried out of the room,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.86,0:18:13.94,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,since you heard the sounds of wine glasses \Nand plates breaking when you opened the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.38,0:18:19.23,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,There was construction taking place \Non the floor below at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.23,0:18:21.20,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,The room was shaking slightly, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.45,0:18:22.80,DCMain,BELLHOP,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.80,0:18:26.58,DCMain,BELLHOP,0000,0000,0000,,Construction starts every day at 9 AM.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.19,0:18:32.20,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You entered this room right \Naround 9 AM, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.20,0:18:32.96,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.97,0:18:39.42,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Then couldn't the vibrations from the \Nwork have caused the glasses and plates...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.42,0:18:41.22,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,...to fall if they were positioned \Njust on the edge of the table?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.52,0:18:45.85,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we try it by putting our \Nphones on the edge of the table?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.92,0:18:48.60,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.87,0:18:53.78,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Is everyone ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.78,0:18:54.86,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.48,0:18:58.76,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.76,0:19:03.28,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Half of them fell, but the other \Nhalf are still on the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.28,0:19:04.58,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.58,0:19:09.41,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Even if the table shakes, there's no telling \Nwhich way they'll shift, so they don't all fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.78,0:19:11.04,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.04,0:19:13.95,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Even if the utensils were placed on the edge,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.95,0:19:16.46,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,the odds that they would fall \Non the floor were 50-50.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.46,0:19:18.55,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,It's not very useful for a trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.76,0:19:19.89,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.35,0:19:24.62,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,And there's no guarantee construction \Nwould start at exactly 9 AM.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.62,0:19:29.66,DCMain,BELLHOP,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, construction was \Nscheduled to start at 9 AM.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.66,0:19:34.14,DCMain,BELLHOP,0000,0000,0000,,It's falling behind schedule, so the hotel has \Nbeen pressuring the construction company to hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.14,0:19:36.69,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,But there's still no guarantee \Nit would start at exactly 9 AM.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.69,0:19:39.79,DCMain,BELLHOP,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, we once received \Na complaint from a guest...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.79,0:19:44.20,DCMain,BELLHOP,0000,0000,0000,,...that construction started a minute early,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.58,0:19:49.26,DCMain,BELLHOP,0000,0000,0000,,so the construction crew's clocks are set \Nto match the hotel's down to the second.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.26,0:19:50.12,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.12,0:19:55.34,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But it's still a coincidence that \Nwe opened the door at exactly 9 AM.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.66,0:19:58.30,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, we opened the door \Nthen because Kokuri-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.30,0:20:01.97,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,...was delayed while calling the bellhop.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.63,0:20:04.97,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What's taking him so long?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.20,0:20:07.58,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What is that director doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.58,0:20:08.85,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.34,0:20:12.85,DCItalic,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. It took a while \Nto explain the situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.15,0:20:15.42,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,And Kokuri-san went to get the bellhop...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.42,0:20:18.86,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,...because he noticed the email from Hotta-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.34,0:20:23.11,DCItalic,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Hotta-san emailed me an hour ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.59,0:20:24.24,DCItalic,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.24,0:20:27.12,Kill2,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,They're going to kill me. Help.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.96,0:20:27.12,DCItalic,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,"Th-They're going to kill me. Help?"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.12,0:20:28.94,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.35,0:20:33.66,DCItalic,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,I-In any case, I'll have a \Nbellhop come unlock the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.66,0:20:37.93,DCItalic,KOKURI,0000,0000,0000,,You stay here so nobody leaves the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.93,0:20:39.22,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.92,0:20:45.39,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,And the email Kokuri-san \Nnoticed was sent an hour ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.39,0:20:47.45,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,If he'd noticed right away,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.45,0:20:51.15,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,we would've entered the room a lot sooner.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.13,0:20:54.77,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,There wouldn't have been time for a trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.00,0:20:55.92,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.92,0:21:01.07,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,So the killer fled from the room when they \Nnoticed us enter and dropped the utensils then.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.33,0:21:03.46,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Detective Takagi?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.55,0:21:08.80,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Something got stuck to my hand \Nwhen I hit the table earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.80,0:21:10.33,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Is this salt?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.25,0:21:12.33,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Salt?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.01,0:21:14.28,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.28,0:21:17.08,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If they used salt, then that explains \Nwhat the inspector said earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.38,0:21:21.30,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And all the coincidences \Nthe old man listed...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.30,0:21:22.76,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.93,0:21:26.93,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,You got salt on the base \Nof your pinkie finger...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.26,0:21:30.68,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,...when you hit the table directly above \Nwhere the glasses and plates had fallen.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.91,0:21:32.05,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.05,0:21:33.31,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.02,0:21:38.35,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It kind of sounds like you're explaining \Nthe details of the situation to someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.55,0:21:40.27,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm not doing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.74,0:21:45.28,DCItalic,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the type of person who organizes their \Nthoughts by asking themselves questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.81,0:21:47.11,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't know?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.31,0:21:49.70,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.70,0:21:51.49,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I had no idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.02,0:24:09.05,DCEpPreview,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.42,0:23:50.90,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-kun, are you sure you saw \Nsomeone run from that window?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.33,0:23:53.66,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I saw it with my own two eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.09,0:23:56.08,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,How is it, Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.08,0:23:58.79,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's a little sticky.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.30,0:24:02.92,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,So you found signs something \Nwas stuck above the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.44,0:24:05.54,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.82,0:24:07.30,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.30,0:24:09.05,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Did you find something?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.05,0:24:15.05,DCNextEp,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,The Spirit Detective's Murder \N(Part Two)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.87,0:24:14.70,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan is\N"The Spirit Detective's Murder, Part Two!"
